  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\nCurrently, all new chats are added to the bottom of the chat list. The chat stays in the same position even if a new message arrives.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nNew chats/chats with new messages are moved to the top of the chat list\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nNew chats are at the bottom of the list; as new messages are received, the position of the chat in the list does not change\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/67952253/8464ed74-b6f4-4e77-84e0-32707ca213e3\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1. UserA adds UserB and UserC to contacts (1-1 chats are created automatically)\r\n2. UserA creates group chats with UserB and UserC (group1, group2)\r\n3. UserA opens the chat screen\r\n4. UserB and UserC send messages to the chats\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly 19/05\r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please, add logs/notes if necessary)\r\n\r\n",
